    <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Vox interlock" hidden="false" id="dd07-9329-b6b3-8daa">
      <profiles>
        <profile name="Command Vox and vox interlocks" typeId="2c11-4ec5-60b9-9d46" typeName="Wargear" hidden="false" id="b0f4-197c-7a3b-f14a">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Summary" typeId="fdcc-276a-cadb-7810">Command vox and vox interlocks allow Units to remove Statuses in the Start Phase.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Description" typeId="516b-bc6f-e52f-aced">If a Unit includes one or more Models with a vox interlock, and there are one or more friendly Models on the Battlefield with a command vox, then the Controlling Player may activate the vox interlock during the Start Phase of their Player Turn. When activated, the Controlling Player may make a Check to remove a single Status from all Models in the Unit that includes the vox interlock. This Check is made using the Characteristics of any one friendly Model on the Battlefield which is part of a Unit containing at least one Model with a command vox, chosen by the Controlling Player (using Cool, unless attempting to remove Routed, in which case Leadership is used). A vox interlock may only be activated once per Player Turn, and each Friendly Model on the Battlefield with a command vox may only be used once per Start Phase as part of this Special Rule.</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
    </selectionEntry>
    <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Auxilia vexilla" hidden="false" id="d328-c90e-9d8a-6613">
      <profiles>
        <profile name="Auxilia vexilla" typeId="2c11-4ec5-60b9-9d46" typeName="Wargear" hidden="false" id="044f-3095-9d9a-0ed3">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Summary" typeId="fdcc-276a-cadb-7810">An Auxilia vexilla increases the Casualty threshold when making Panic Checks for a Unit in the Shooting Phase from 25% to 50%.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Description" typeId="516b-bc6f-e52f-aced"/>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
    </selectionEntry>
